67
00:05:42,180 --> 00:05:50,804
[SPEAKER_06]: So we are looking to financially close on the project in February of 23 and start construction soon thereafter.

68
00:05:51,424 --> 00:05:55,366
[SPEAKER_06]: We have an anticipated completion date of about June of 2025.

69
00:05:57,327 --> 00:06:00,028
[SPEAKER_06]: So we're looking at about two and a half years of construction.

70
00:06:00,409 --> 00:06:03,650
[SPEAKER_06]: And it's going to be a rolling construction process.

71
00:06:04,471 --> 00:06:06,292
[SPEAKER_06]: It's gonna be occupied construction.

72
00:06:06,752 --> 00:06:12,395
[SPEAKER_06]: We're starting from the top floors on the 11th and 10th, ninth floor, and then working our way down.

73
00:06:13,075 --> 00:06:16,757
[SPEAKER_06]: We are in the process of vacating those floors right now.

74
00:06:17,477 --> 00:06:23,020
[SPEAKER_06]: And as the 11th and 10th floors get complete, residents from seventh, eighth, and ninth will move up.

75
00:06:23,580 --> 00:06:27,542
[SPEAKER_06]: And then we'll work our way down all the way through the building.

76
00:06:27,602 --> 00:06:33,124
[SPEAKER_06]: And there will be a buffer floor between construction and where the residents are living.

77
00:06:33,704 --> 00:06:39,807
[SPEAKER_06]: So we anticipate having two active floors of construction with a buffer floor.

78
00:06:39,927 --> 00:06:42,488
[SPEAKER_06]: So we're always going to try to have three floors in play.

79
00:06:43,869 --> 00:06:49,211
[SPEAKER_06]: So the start construction would take place on the 10th and 11th floor with the ninth floor as the buffer.

